// TODO Wave 2.2 follow-up — visual regression for the inline-style codemod
//
// STILL DEFERRED as of W2.5 (PR2 close-out). The codemod
// (`scripts/codemod-inline-style-to-tw.ts`) replaced 146 inline
// `style="..."` attributes and 5 `<style>` blocks with Tailwind
// utilities + Svelte `style:` directives + lifts into
// `apps/web/src/app.css`. The translations are semantically equivalent
// in theory (e.g. `style="color: var(--landing-oxide)"` ↔
// `class="text-[var(--landing-oxide)]"`), but Tailwind v4's specificity
// ordering vs inline-style specificity is not 100% identical when
// other utilities target the same property. A snapshot pass on the
// pages with the most rewrites (the landing page and `landing/demo.svelte`)
// would catch any visual drift introduced by the sweep.
//
// What this spec should do once unblocked:
//
//   import { expect, test } from '@playwright/test';
//
//   const routes = ['/', '/login', '/jobs', '/sitemap.xml'];
//   for (const path of routes) {
//     test(`visual: ${path}`, async ({ page }) => {
//       await page.goto(path);
//       await page.waitForLoadState('networkidle');
//       await expect(page).toHaveScreenshot({
//         maxDiffPixelRatio: 0.001,
//         fullPage: true,
//       });
//     });
//   }
//
// Why it's deferred (re-evaluated in W2.5):
//   1) Visual snapshots require a stable baseline image, which needs
//      to be generated on a CI machine (different fonts/AA on local
//      Linux vs CI Chromium would always diff). Baseline gen needs a
//      one-shot CI job before this spec is even useful.
//   2) The auth-gated routes need the `loginAs` helpers from
//      `test/infrastructure/e2e/_helpers/auth.ts`, which assume the
//      seeded backend (profile-services) is up — every PR2 wave was
//      scoped to patch-careers-ui only and the seeded backend is
//      provisioned per-CI-run, not per-local-session.
//   3) Promoted out of W2.5 deliverables; PR3 (or later) will own the
//      Playwright snapshot infrastructure end-to-end (baseline runner,
//      CI gate, diff review flow). Adding 4 isolated snapshots here
//      without that wiring would be orphan tooling.
//
// Open file with `.todo` extension so Playwright's `testDir: './test'`
// glob (which only picks up `*.spec.ts`) doesn't pick it up. Rename
